Parents and members of the EFF clash at Brackenfell High School in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - One person has been arrested outside Brackenfell High School in Cape Town where members of the EFF clashed with parents on Monday. The 39-year-old male has been arrested after discharging a firearm during clashes between EFF members and parents of Brackenfell High School. The school is embroiled in a racism row after it allegedly held a private function without inviting learners of colour. READ: EFF members, parents clash outside Cape Town school One parent, who asked for us to hide her identity, says racism is rife at the school. Parents and former pupils have also vowed to use force if provoked by the EFF.
                           
The South African Police Service in the province says police will remain on the scene until calm is restored.